cc:Work.dc:title: BRCC Block Buster (remix)
cc:Work.dc:description:
The Big Red Computer Club (circa 1980s - early 1990s) was a monthly newsletter style users group for Apple II. Members could mail order public domain software for a small fee to cover the cost of the disks and distribution. These letters ("font") comes from one of their Print Shop clipart sets.
